stu001.What are P-values?: P-values are a statistical measure used to determine whether the observed results of a study are statistically significant. It quantifies the probability of observing results at least as extreme as those in the data, assuming that the null hypothesis is true. A smaller p-value indicates stronger evidence against the null hypothesis.

The Central Limit Theorem states that the distribution of sample means is normal.

stu001.What is regression analysis?: Regression analysis is a technique for classifying data into different categories based on statistical models.
